articles.title: Perez: Red Bull F1 will "struggle to show its strengths" in Monaco - Motorsport.com
articles.description: Sergio Perez expects Monaco to be a more difficult circuit for his normally dominant Red Bull Formula 1 team as he and Max Verstappen "will struggle a bit to show our strengths".
articles.content:
Red Bull has impressed with its excellent stability through fast corners and high top speeds, but its RB19's qualities will play less of a role through the principality's twisty streets.

articles.title: Verstappen: Honda's Aston Martin F1 move "a bit of a shame" - Motorsport.com
articles.description: Max Verstappen says seeing Honda team up with Aston Martin in Formula 1 is "a bit of a shame" and it was "unfortunate" how its collaboration with Red Bull ended.
articles.content:
It was revealed on Wednesday that Aston Martin is to become Honda's official works partner in 2026, having previously announced its exit from F1 in 2021.
